Customer credit limit rule - current implementation

Scope
- This rule is currently enforced in the Contract module.
- Source implementation:
  - src/main/java/com/g90/backend/modules/contract/integration/ContractCreditGateway.java
  - src/main/java/com/g90/backend/modules/contract/service/ContractServiceImpl.java
  - src/main/java/com/g90/backend/exception/ContractCreditLimitExceededException.java

Data source
- creditLimit: read from customers.credit_limit
- currentDebt: calculated from unpaid invoices
  - total outstanding = (invoice.total_amount + vat_amount) - allocated payments
  - only invoices with status not equal to PAID are counted

Computed values
- availableCredit = creditLimit - currentDebt
- projectedDebt = currentDebt + contract.totalAmount

Exceeded condition
- Credit limit is enforced only when creditLimit > 0
- If projectedDebt > creditLimit, the contract is considered over limit

Behavior by API flow
- Preview contract:
  - does not block
  - returns warning: "Projected debt exceeds current credit limit"
- Create contract:
  - blocks when projectedDebt > creditLimit
  - throws CONTRACT_CREDIT_LIMIT_EXCEEDED
- Update draft contract:
  - blocks with the same rule as create
- Submit contract:
  - checks again before submission
  - blocks when projectedDebt > creditLimit

Special case
- If creditLimit <= 0, the current implementation treats the customer as UNLIMITED for enforcement purposes

Related display / risk behavior
- approval review includes a reason when projected debt exceeds available credit
- credit risk level:
  - UNLIMITED if creditLimit <= 0
  - HIGH if projectedDebt > creditLimit
  - MEDIUM if projectedDebt uses at least 80% of creditLimit
  - LOW otherwise

Not implemented currently
- No separate approval workflow for over-credit contracts
- No partial tolerance or soft-threshold behavior
- No distinction between create-draft allowed and submit blocked; current rule blocks create/update and submit

Current exception
- code: CONTRACT_CREDIT_LIMIT_EXCEEDED
- message: Customer credit limit would be exceeded
